Topic: What is SSB & Officer Like Qualities (OLQs)
🪖 What is SSB?

Services Selection Board (SSB) is a 5-day personality assessment, not an exam.
It checks how you think, act, lead, and live—to see if you’re fit to be an officer in the Armed Forces.

👉 No mugging. No bookish marks.
👉 They test natural behaviour under different situations.

🎯 What SSB REALLY WANTS

Not toppers. Not bodybuilders.
They want potential officers who:

Take responsibility

Work with people

Stay calm under pressure

Act honestly and decisively

This potential is measured through OLQs.

⭐ Officer Like Qualities (OLQs)

SSB uses 15 OLQs, grouped into 4 factors.

1️⃣ Planning & Organising

Effective Intelligence

Reasoning Ability

Organising Ability

👉 Think clearly, plan smartly, act logically.

2️⃣ Social Adjustment

Social Adaptability

Cooperation

👉 Team player, not a lone hero.

3️⃣ Social Effectiveness

Initiative

Self-Confidence

Speed of Decision

Ability to Influence Group

Liveliness

👉 Leadership + energy + confidence.

4️⃣ Dynamic Factors

Determination

Courage

Stamina

👉 Mental + physical toughness.

🧠 BIGGEST MYTH (BREAK THIS TODAY)

❌ “I must behave differently in SSB”
❌ “I should write ideal answers”

✅ SSB rewards REAL, TRAINED YOU
Consistency across tests matters more than perfection.

🔍 Where OLQs Are Tested
Test	What they observe
OIR	Logic, clarity
PPDT / TAT	Thinking, responsibility
WAT / SRT	Attitude, decision making
GTO	Teamwork, leadership
Interview	Honesty, self-awareness
